The much-awaited Peller Unity Cup (PUC) Season two kicks off tomorrow with ex-internationals Joseph Dosu and Femi Opabunmi pledging to reward the most outstanding players of the competition. The ex-Super Eagles players who promised to watch all the matches promised to introduce the best players in the game to European clubs. All 10 local governments in the Oke-Ogun area of Oyo state are participating in the football tournament and they are Olorunsogo, Orelope, Kajola, Iwajowa, Iseyin, Itesiwaju, Irepo, Olorunsogo, Saki East, and Saki West. The promoter of the football tournament, Shina Peller representing Iseyin/Itesiwaju/Kajola/Iwajowa Federal Constituency of Oyo state said the maiden edition of the football competition, founded in 2017, was to commemorate the 20th anniversary of the death of the great magician, Mashood Folorunsho Abiola Atanda a.k.a. Prof. Peller.   Neymar eyes MLS after leaving PSG     Curtain falls on Beijing Winter Olympics     Leicester to open Ndidi contract talks amid Villa’s link   The first edition of the competition was sponsored by Aquila Group founded by the lawmaker. - Advertisement - The football tournament features 440 players, and 20 teams from the 10 local governments of Oke-Ogun in Oyo state ends on March 27, 2022. Peller explained that the competition was aimed to engage the youths as well as to identify and promote football talents from the grassroots level. “We all gather here today for multi-purpose, but topping the list of the reasons we are here is my utmost desire to promote peace, unity, and progress of my people – the great people of the Oke Ogun region. “Football, being a universal language that everyone understands, helps connect people together irrespective of tribal, political, or religious belief. It helps to unite people. This is what the PUC stands for; it is a unifying tool for the people of Oke Ogun,” Peller added. SPONSORED